title: Oncocyte Signs Leading Transplant Centers in US and Germany
summary: Oncocyte Corporation (Nasdaq: OCX) announced that its new customers include two leading transplant university hospitals in the U.S. and Germany. Both have entered into agreements with the Company to utilize GraftAssure™, the Company’s research-use-only assay. Graft Assay can detect early evidence of graft organ damage in patients’ blood. The Company also announced that it is on track and has submitted its plan for an IVD version of its kitted test to the FDA.

title: If You'd Invested $150 in Rivian Stock 3 Years Ago, Here's How Much You'd Have Today
summary: Rivian (RIVN -1.29%) stock has massive long-term upside potential. Its current market cap is just $13 billion -- $800 billion less than its biggest competitor, Tesla. With new mass-market models on the way, we could see Rivian's valuation soar over the coming years.

title: Here's Why United Airlines Stock Soared Nearly 30% in September
summary: The airline industry assuaged investor fears in the fall. Shares in United Airlines (UAL -0.11%) soared by 29.6% in September. Wall Street has United Airlines generating $9.80 in earnings per share in 2024.

title: Oncocyte Corporation Announces $10.2 Million Private Placement of Securities Priced At-The-Market Under Nasdaq Rules - OncoCyte  ( NASDAQ:OCX )
summary: The gross proceeds to the Company from the private placement are expected to be approximately $10.2 million. The Company intends to use the net proceeds for working capital and general corporate purposes. The private placement was priced "at-the-market" under the rules and regulations of The Nasdaq Stock Market LLC.

title: Oncocyte Corporation Announces $10.2 Million Private Placement of Securities Priced At-The-Market Under Nasdaq Rules
summary: Oncocyte Corporation (Nasdaq: OCX) announces that it has entered into a securities purchase agreement with new and existing investors. The gross proceeds to the Company from the private placement are expected to be approximately $10.2 million. The Company intends to use the net proceeds for working capital and general corporate purposes.

title: Sandfire Resources America Inc. Announces Incentive Plan Grants
summary: Sandfire Resources America Inc. announces the grant of a total of 1,774,306 restricted share units (“RSUs”) to certain officers of the Company in accordance with the Company’s long-term incentive plan. The RSUs will vest in three equal tranches, on July 1, 2025, 2026 and 2027.

title: NOVONIX to Host Third Quarter 2024 Operations Update and Participate in OTC Small Cap Growth Conference - NOVONIX  ( NASDAQ:NVX ) , NOVONIX  ( OTC:NVNXF )
summary: NOVONIX plans to release its Quarterly Activities Report for the quarter ended September 30, 2024. Dr. Chris Burns, CEO of NOVONIX, will also provide prepared remarks on the quarter. The Company is also scheduled to participate in the OTC Small Cap Growth Virtual Investor Conference.

title: NOVONIX to Host Third Quarter 2024 Operations Update and Participate in OTC Small Cap Growth Conference
summary: NOVONIX Limited will release its Quarterly Activities Report for the quarter ended September 30, 2024. Dr. Chris Burns, CEO of NOVONIX, will also provide prepared remarks on the quarter. The Company will also participate in the OTC Small Cap Growth Virtual Investor Conference on October 10, 2024, at 10:00 am EDT.

title: Grupo Aeroportuario Del Pacifico Reports in September 2024 a Passenger Traffic Decrease of 3.9% Compared to 2023
summary: Grupo Aeroportuario del Pacífico, S.A.B. de C.V. (GAP) operates 12 airports throughout Mexico’s Pacific region. In October 2018, GAP entered into a concession agreement for the Norman Manley International Airport in Kingston, Jamaica. GAP has implemented a “whistleblower” program, which allows complainants to anonymously report activities that involve criminal conduct.

title: Moore Law, PLLC Encourages Amgen, Inc. Investors to Contact Law Firm
summary: Moore Law, PLLC, a securities and shareholder law firm located on Wall Street, is investigating potential claims against: Amgen Inc. The case argues that shareholders were misled when Amgen allegedly concealed the risk of owing billions to the Internal Revenue Service.

title: Why Chinese Stocks Continued to Zoom Higher on Wednesday
summary: Many top Chinese stocks kept climbing higher, successfully surmounting Hump Day. Electric vehicle (EV) maker Li Auto (LI 3.60%) rose by nearly 5% on the day. Tencent Music Entertainment Group (TME -2.11%) increased at an almost 8% clip.

title: Ohio Cannabis Market Soars To $76M In Less Than 2 Months But Michigan Remains The Leader
summary: Ohio's recreational marijuana industry is gaining momentum, with sales reaching $76.3 million as of the end of September. In under two months, Ohio's legal weed market has moved over 8,813 pounds of plant materials and 1.2 million units of manufactured products.
